## Building a Sudoku Board with Validation in React

**Mental model:** A 9×9 grid of digit strings plus a `given` mask (which cells are fixed). Editing a non-given cell accepts only 1–9. Validation is *derived*: scan every row, column, and 3×3 box for duplicate digits and collect the conflicting cell keys. Cells in that set render red.

### Step 1 — Board + given mask
```jsx
const [board, setBoard] = useState(PUZZLE.map((r) => [...r]));
const given = PUZZLE.map((r) => r.map((v) => v !== ''));
```

### Step 2 — Edit only non-given, digits only
```jsx
const set = (r, c, v) => {
  if (given[r][c]) return;
  if (v !== '' && !/^[1-9]$/.test(v)) return;
  setBoard((b) => b.map((row, i) => row.map((cell, j) => (i === r && j === c ? v : cell))));
};
```

### Step 3 — Derive conflicts
For each group (9 rows, 9 cols, 9 boxes), any digit appearing twice marks all its cells.

```jsx
const conflicts = useMemo(() => findConflicts(board), [board]);
// findConflicts groups cell coords by digit within each unit; size>1 => conflict
```

### Step 4 — Render with box borders + red conflicts
```jsx
<input value={board[r][c]} readOnly={given[r][c]}
  style={{ color: conflicts.has(`${r},${c}`) ? '#dc2626' : '#111' }} />
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Editing a given cell | Blocked by the mask. |
| Non-digit input | Rejected by the regex. |
| Solved check | No conflicts and no empty cells. |

**Interview tip:** Deriving conflicts by bucketing cell coordinates per digit within each unit (row/col/box) — rather than O(n²) pairwise comparison — is the tidy, scalable validation approach to articulate.

