## Building a Sudoku Board with Validation in Vue 3

**Mental model:** A 9×9 grid of digit strings plus a `given` mask. Editing a non-given cell accepts only 1–9. Conflicts are a `computed`: scan each row, column, and 3×3 box for duplicate digits and collect conflicting cell keys; those render red.

### Step 1 — Board + given mask
```js
const board = ref(PUZZLE.map((r) => [...r]));
const given = PUZZLE.map((r) => r.map((v) => v !== ''));
```

### Step 2 — Edit guard
```js
function set(r, c, v) {
  if (given[r][c]) return;
  const d = v.slice(-1);
  if (d !== '' && !/^[1-9]$/.test(d)) return;
  board.value[r][c] = d;
}
```

### Step 3 — Conflicts as computed
```js
const conflicts = computed(() => findConflicts(board.value));
// bucket cell coords by digit per unit; any bucket > 1 marks all its cells
```

### Step 4 — Render with box borders
```vue
<input :value="board[r][c]" :readonly="given[r][c]"
  :style="{ color: conflicts.has(r + ',' + c) ? '#dc2626' : '#111' }" />
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Given cell | Blocked by mask. |
| Non-digit | Rejected by regex. |
| Solved | No conflicts and no empties. |

**Interview tip:** A `computed` that buckets coordinates by digit per unit is the clean validation — recomputes on each edit and avoids pairwise comparisons.

