## Building a Sudoku Board with Validation in Angular

**Mental model:** A 9×9 grid of digit strings plus a `given` mask. Editing a non-given cell accepts only 1–9. Conflicts come from a getter: scan rows, columns, and 3×3 boxes for duplicate digits, collecting conflicting cell keys; those render red. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them).

### Step 1 — Board + given mask
```typescript
board: string[][] = this.PUZZLE.map((r) => [...r]);
given: boolean[][] = this.PUZZLE.map((r) => r.map((v) => v !== ''));
```

### Step 2 — Edit guard
```typescript
set(r: number, c: number, v: string): void {
  if (this.given[r][c]) { return; }
  const d = v.slice(-1);
  if (d !== '' && !/^[1-9]$/.test(d)) { return; }
  this.board[r][c] = d;
}
```

### Step 3 — Conflicts getter
```typescript
get conflicts(): Set<string> { return findConflicts(this.board); }
// bucket coords by digit per unit; any bucket > 1 marks all its cells
```

### Step 4 — Render
```html
<input [value]="board[r][c]" [readonly]="given[r][c]"
  [style.color]="conflicts.has(r + ',' + c) ? '#dc2626' : '#111'" />
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Given cell | Blocked by mask. |
| Non-digit | Rejected by regex. |
| Solved | No conflicts and no empties. |

**Interview tip:** Bucketing coordinates by digit per unit (row/col/box) in the getter is the clean validation — and caching it (memo/computed) would avoid recomputing on every change-detection pass for large boards.

